Interface IEnrichmentBatchModule


  • public interface IEnrichmentBatchModule
    The interface enrichment developers need to implement this interface to use JARs as enrichment modules in batch mode

    acp

    • Method Detail

      • onStageInitialize

        void onStageInitialize(IEnrichmentModuleContext context,
                       DataBucketBean bucket,
                       EnrichmentControlMetadataBean control,
                       scala.Tuple2<IEnrichmentBatchModule.ProcessingStage,IEnrichmentBatchModule.ProcessingStage> previous_next,
                       Optional<List<String>> next_grouping_fields)
        Called when the stage (eg map or reduce) is starting Note that this is only called once per set of onObjectBatches - if multiple instances of the batch module are spawned (eg when grouping) then clone(IEnrichmentBatchModule) is called.
        Parameters:
        context - - a context
        bucket - - the bucket for which this enrichment is taking place
        control - - the control metadata for the stage
        previous_next - - the previous and next stages of the processing (note input/input is pre-deduplication/merge, output/output is post-deduplication/merge), note that prev only appears as grouping if the grouping key was the same
        next_grouping_fields - - if the next stage requires grouped fields, this is the list. If it's present but empty, this means the stage has automated fields and the needs to be grouped on a per "emit" basis.

      • onObjectBatch

        void onObjectBatch(Stream<scala.Tuple2<Long,IBatchRecord>> batch,
                   Optional<Integer> batch_size,
                   Optional<com.fasterxml.jackson.databind.JsonNode> grouping_key)
        A batch of objects is ready for processing (unless one of the context.emitObjects is called, the object will be discarded)
        Parameters:
        batch - a stream of (id, object, lazy binary stream) for processing
        batch_size - - if this is present then the stream corresponds to a set of records of known size, if not then it's a stream of unknown size (this normally only occurs
        grouping_key - - if this stage has records grouped by a grouping key (represented as a JsonNode) - note that if prev stage is also grouping this indicates an intermediate grouping took place (Eg combine)

      • onStageComplete

        void onStageComplete(boolean is_original)
        Called when a stage is complete - enables tidying up and similar (flushing) Is called on every instance of the IEnrichmentBatchModule spawned
        Parameters:
        is_original - - the instance on which onStageInitialize was called (always called last, ie can clean up any shared resources)

      • cloneForNewGrouping

        default IEnrichmentBatchModule cloneForNewGrouping()
        This is called once per key in reduce type cases Can be left blank if no state is required(the same object will be returned), otherwise can create a new object and copy across any initializations from onStageInitialize
        Returns:
        the instance of IEnrichmentBatchModule on which onStageComplete is called

      • validateModule

        default Collection<BasicMessageBean> validateModule(IEnrichmentModuleContext context,
                                                    DataBucketBean bucket,
                                                    EnrichmentControlMetadataBean control)
        An optional interface that analytic/enrichment technologies can (optionally) invoke to check whether the module is likely to error on initialization
        Parameters:
        context - - a context
        bucket - - the bucket for which this enrichment is taking place
        control - - the control metadata for the stage
        Returns:
        A validation message if there is anything to report - a failed validation occurs when the BasicMessageBean is present *and* has success()==false
